1e3ee593-acbe-4b1f-8b83-8cb6fc56bedb.do_description: To make the output, you have to...complete the same pattern with the two incomplete patterns, going in the same direction as the line dictates, with one space between each pattern continuing to the border.
1e3ee593-acbe-4b1f-8b83-8cb6fc56bedb.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input size
1e3ee593-acbe-4b1f-8b83-8cb6fc56bedb.see_description: In the input, you should see...one completed pattern and two incomplete patterns of different colors.

46dd6275-940e-43fc-a43c-042de3ca022c.do_description: To make the output, you have to... copy the input grid. Then build onto the smaller shapes so that they become the same as the original main shape, but do not change their color. Then, continue to draw the same shape in the same color and at the same distance until you reach the end of the grid. So if it is a square, keep adding squares at an equal distance until you reach the edge of the grid. If it is a plus sign or any other shape, do the same. Repeat this in any direction where a small shape is near the original big shape.
46dd6275-940e-43fc-a43c-042de3ca022c.grid_description: The output grid size... is the same as the input grid.
46dd6275-940e-43fc-a43c-042de3ca022c.see_description: In the input, you should see... a large colored shape and smaller colored shapes next to, above, below or diagonal from the largest shape.

62882c5d-7d04-4c56-b333-24901459c8d8.do_description: To make the output, you have to...complete the same pattern in the differing color all the way to the edge of the grid along the same direction or line that it starts at,
62882c5d-7d04-4c56-b333-24901459c8d8.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input size
62882c5d-7d04-4c56-b333-24901459c8d8.see_description: In the input, you should see...a design pattern with incomplete patterns in different colors next to it on a black background

76dafa84-a1ff-4569-99ba-611b56ae8f17.do_description: To make the output, you have to... 1st: make the pink and blue objects look exactly like the grey object with the original pink part on the bottom left of the object and the blue on the top.2nd.  repeat the pink object upwards diagonal of 3 squares (it will be cut off by the top just do what you can.3rd: repeat the blue object diagonal by one square (the 3rd will be cut off a bit)
76dafa84-a1ff-4569-99ba-611b56ae8f17.see_description: In the input, you should see...a small grey object with six grey squares in an almost square pattern with a black hole of one square in the middle, an object of two pink squares to the top right of it and a small object of 3 blue squares to the bottom right of it.

79119373-ce69-4bf8-9eb2-75259e08c6c4.do_description: To make the output, you have to... replicate the reference shape, using the color of the other  blocks as a start point and then replicate that pattern to the edge of the grid, even if it needs a incomplete shape.
79119373-ce69-4bf8-9eb2-75259e08c6c4.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same size.
79119373-ce69-4bf8-9eb2-75259e08c6c4.see_description: In the input, you should see...a reference shape, which will be the shape with the most blocks, with various colored blocks to its sides.

a786e225-6f75-4103-8e7f-e4f38c7d91bc.do_description: To make the output, you have to...replicate the central pattern for each surrounding incomplete pattern, using the color of the surrounding pattern, along the same direction of the surrounding pattern, and reproduce it as necessary until the end of the square
a786e225-6f75-4103-8e7f-e4f38c7d91bc.grid_description: The output grid size...same as input size
a786e225-6f75-4103-8e7f-e4f38c7d91bc.see_description: In the input, you should see...a central, complete pattern with incomplete patterns of differing colors around it

f273fb6d-f7c8-4608-b7e4-76e30c6c035a.do_description: To make the output, you have to...complete the same pattern in the differing color all the way to the edge of the grid along the same direction or line that it starts at.
f273fb6d-f7c8-4608-b7e4-76e30c6c035a.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input size
f273fb6d-f7c8-4608-b7e4-76e30c6c035a.see_description: In the input, you should see...a design pattern with incomplete patterns in different colors next to it on a black background

f6a22800-7805-44dd-a116-7c3a887b9a2b.do_description: To make the output, you have to...duplicate the larger shape using the color and location of each smaller shape.  Once you have done that, you will need to continue the shape pattern to the edges of the grid.  That is make more duplicates being spaced the same distance and direction until you hit the edge of the grid.
f6a22800-7805-44dd-a116-7c3a887b9a2b.grid_description: The output grid size...stays the same
f6a22800-7805-44dd-a116-7c3a887b9a2b.see_description: In the input, you should see...a larger shape and smaller shapes

fbd854fb-cb92-4a97-b67f-8d791bb25bd0.do_description: To make the output, you have to...complete the pattern for the other two colors which are blue and pink to be just like shape of gray and from there follow the same space and continue the draw to the end.
fbd854fb-cb92-4a97-b67f-8d791bb25bd0.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the output
fbd854fb-cb92-4a97-b67f-8d791bb25bd0.see_description: In the input, you should see...incomplete patterns in gray, pink and blue.
